After racing for 12 long days through the desert and covering over 7,500km, Sam Sunderland secured his third career podium at the Dakar with an admirable top-three result.

Matthias Walkner finished inside the top 10 despite an early setback, and rally rookie Daniel Sanders impressed the entire paddock with his fourth place result.

node.text:
Josep Garcia completes the perfect weekend in Estonia, securing his second-consecutive EnduroGP win.

In an incredibly close battle right to the finish, Josep went into the day's final Super Test just under two seconds down on the leader. Posting an amazing time, two-and-a-half-seconds faster than his rival, Josep clinched the stage win and with it, the Grand Prix victory!

Red Bull KTM's attention now looks to Sweden and round four of the FIM Enduro World Championship, starting this Thursday, July 22.

Photos: @future7media

@mxgp | Vialle to miss Dutch MXGP to continue hand injury recovery

MX2 World Champion Tom Vialle will not line-up in Oss this weekend for round four of 2021 MXGP as the small fracture in his right hand has not yet healed sufficiently. The winner of the season-opening race in Russia is hoping to attempt the Czech Grand Prix the following weekend.

"The Grand Prix in Oss came just a bit too soon," he said. "The bone has not healed 100% so we still need to wait a little before practicing and racing again. We will make another check-up next week and I hope to ride in Loket.”
